Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.47,0:00:15.08,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I want to shine on you,\Nand always like that dazzling sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.38,0:00:18.75,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I will defend you\Nfrom all the darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.85,0:00:24.75,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is the truth from my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.76,0:00:39.54,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If only our hearts could connect,\NI could get you to believe me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.64,0:00:46.31,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you can't\Nsee it now, don't lose it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.48,0:00:54.25,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your kindness won't be in vain.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.08,0:01:01.66,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be carried aloft by the wind\Nto somewhere that isn't here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.06,0:01:08.77,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You'll cross the sea and cross time,\Nand I know you'll blossom one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.93,0:01:15.41,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever the day,\NI'll be there for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.84,0:01:22.05,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I hope I can watch over you\Nlike the sun for all time.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.05,0:01:32.02,OP,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is the truth from my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.00,0:01:50.74,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There wasn't much snow this winter.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.78,0:02:01.48,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, I see.\NNyunga Ro Im died, did he?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.12,0:02:11.13,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 23\NIn Search of the Shigu Salua
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.60,0:02:19.44,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. We weren't able to decipher\Neverything before your departure.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.74,0:02:22.57,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all. It's enough\Nthat we found a way...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.57,0:02:25.07,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...to protect the prince\Nfrom the egg-eater.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.51,0:02:28.98,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That is true.\NEven a demon from Nayug...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.98,0:02:31.51,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...can be defeated\Nif struck at its weak point.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.85,0:02:35.32,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.82,0:02:39.66,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If we uncover anything new,\NI shall dispatch a rider to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.39,0:02:41.66,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You should go.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.81,0:02:59.68,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So, the time has finally\Ncome for you to set off.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.08,0:03:02.65,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Your Majesty.\NI shall save Prince Chagum's life...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.65,0:03:04.65,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...even if the price\Nshould be my own.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.42,0:03:07.35,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Good luck to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.55,0:03:11.95,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,However, you must\Nreturn safely to us as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.16,0:03:17.63,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You have already become\Nindispensable to this country.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.86,0:03:22.13,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I will take my leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.82,0:04:21.46,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter, Chagum?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.41,0:04:46.68,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Torogai!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.68,0:04:50.72,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Torogai? You're riding\Nthat donkey again?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.05,0:04:54.49,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it insisted on coming with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.53,0:04:59.86,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.84,0:05:10.04,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're starting to\Nlook like a man, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.44,0:05:14.78,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Chagum is 12 now, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.08,0:05:22.52,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I had a feeling that\Nthis might happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.22,0:05:24.39,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.39,0:05:26.69,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.02,0:05:30.36,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You can't walk around in\Nchildren's clothes forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.66,0:05:33.00,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Change into those,\Nand let's have a look at you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.13,0:05:37.97,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, Tanda...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.97,0:05:41.44,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...also had a growth spurt\Naround that age, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.87,0:05:42.71,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I did?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.27,0:05:47.34,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You sure did. Till then, you\Nwere just my cute little brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.95,0:05:50.95,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's when it occurred to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.58,0:05:55.35,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The passage of time\Nchanges all sorts of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.62,0:06:00.22,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shoo.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.39,0:06:02.99,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.10,0:06:13.64,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Here, catch. That's what\Nyou asked me to get for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.02,0:06:35.22,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You weren't a prince\Nfor nothing, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.63,0:06:36.76,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do I look strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.83,0:06:41.93,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It looks good on you.\NYou look like a fine young man now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.43,0:06:44.83,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.18,0:06:57.58,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A sword's weight is a life's weight.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.11,0:07:01.32,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The sword you hold represents\Nyour life as well as your death.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.65,0:07:03.15,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Whenever you draw it...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.15,0:07:06.92,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...do so in the knowledge that you\Nhave entrusted your life to its blade.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.26,0:07:11.93,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's a saying we have in Kanbal.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.09,0:07:14.63,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's recited during the\Ncoming-of-age ritual...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.63,0:07:17.20,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...when a son receives\Nhis first short sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.20,0:07:19.04,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, the father\Nis supposed to say it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.24,0:07:25.04,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Balsa.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.59,0:07:39.72,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Chagum, what's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.32,0:07:42.59,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I was summoned.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.66,0:07:43.66,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,By whom?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.53,0:07:45.73,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's not a voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.30,0:07:50.80,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's a powerful sensation like I'm being\Npulled by a string that I can't see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.60,0:07:54.44,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The egg was\Nwhispering to you, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.21,0:07:58.21,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So, where do you want to go?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.84,0:08:03.08,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.81,0:08:07.28,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So, the land of feasting\Nis one of the springs...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.28,0:08:10.22,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...that feed into the Aoyumi\Nlike it said in the official history?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.95,0:08:13.06,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All right, boy,\Nshow us the way there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.09,0:08:19.33,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's move out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.19,0:09:21.69,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Look at that motherly\Nexpression on your face.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.93,0:09:24.23,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is that wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.63,0:09:30.30,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Assuming that you survive all this...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.73,0:09:33.27,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...what do you plan\Nto do afterwards?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.00,0:09:38.21,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There's something to be said\Nfor settling down in one place.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.21,0:09:42.45,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Having children and raising\Nthem is enjoyable enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.85,0:09:46.72,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You make it sound like\Nyou've had children of your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.98,0:09:48.62,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've had three of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.45,0:09:50.72,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.92,0:09:53.32,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why would I lie about\Nsomething like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.76,0:09:56.99,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lately...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.03,0:10:02.50,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lately, I've had\Nthis recurring dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.03,0:10:04.07,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A dream?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.33,0:10:05.27,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.24,0:10:07.47,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What sort of dream?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.58,0:10:19.28,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.22,0:10:27.56,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Tanda...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.46,0:10:32.06,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Did you ever get an\Nanswer from Balsa?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.66,0:10:33.83,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Answer to what?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.83,0:10:36.67,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You know, what you said\Nto her back at Hunter's Hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.67,0:10:39.27,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,About the three of us\Nliving together.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.74,0:10:41.14,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You were listening?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.11,0:10:51.78,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what to say...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.68,0:10:55.42,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You should just marry her\Nas soon as you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.79,0:10:58.55,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't make it sound so easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.05,0:11:02.69,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Balsa and I both\Nhave complicated lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.43,0:11:06.03,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you talking\Nabout Balsa's oath?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.60,0:11:11.27,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, there's that, but we've\Nprobably spent too much time together.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.30,0:11:15.84,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's like we've gradually\Ngrown farther apart or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.34,0:11:25.88,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In the old days, my feelings for her\Nwere hot like the summer sunshine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.02,0:11:27.78,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Over the years, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.78,0:11:31.55,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...they've changed...\Nturned warm like the autumn wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.99,0:11:36.13,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, that's why I'm fine with\Nkeeping things the way they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.43,0:11:40.90,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.46,0:11:44.00,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Look, let's just forget\Nabout this, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.50,0:11:49.77,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how much I mull over it,\Nthis is one thing I can't solve on my own.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.54,0:11:52.91,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then why don't I go\Nask Balsa for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.38,0:11:58.81,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When did you get\Nso decisive, Chagum?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.58,0:12:03.19,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And here I am, scared out of\Nmy wits over just about everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.72,0:12:05.02,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I realized something.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.02,0:12:10.89,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if I die, I know I'll be able to\Nleave behind a legacy, so it's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.03,0:12:15.73,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since Balsa\Ntold me all about Jiguro...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.73,0:12:17.73,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...I've been able to\Nlook at life that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.01,0:12:30.01,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Moribito Guardian of the Spirit
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.05,0:12:44.09,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We're not to engage the\Nspear-wielder? I don't follow you, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.79,0:12:47.60,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Our interests coincide with hers.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.16,0:12:50.87,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There is no longer\Nany reason to fight her.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.80,0:12:54.80,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In addition, there are Prince\NChagum's feelings to consider.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.54,0:12:57.77,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.22,0:13:07.25,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Master Shuga.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.45,0:13:11.22,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As per your instructions,\Nthree of our best archers...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.22,0:13:13.46,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...have been concealed\Non the return trail.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.03,0:13:17.13,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.40,0:13:22.36,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But are you sure that's\Nwhat you want to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.60,0:13:26.00,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We have no choice.\NIt is what the mikado ordered.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.25,0:13:39.85,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There isn't much water.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.08,0:13:43.69,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like the first signs of drought\Nare starting to show themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.93,0:14:25.79,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So, up ahead is the\Npromised land, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.14,0:14:39.81,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Look at all those shigu salua flowers.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.38,0:14:43.91,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Aoike? This is\Nthe land of feasting?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.62,0:14:47.82,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.37,0:15:07.80,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mistress Torogai, we have come\Nto fulfil our end of the bargain.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.14,0:15:11.24,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'm glad to see that\Nyou didn't come empty-handed!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.39,0:15:26.19,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Crown Prince Chagum.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.62,0:15:30.29,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We have come to assist\Nin the birth of the water spirit...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.29,0:15:36.10,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...and to welcome you back as\Nthe hero who saved Shin-Yogo.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.97,0:15:44.21,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shuga, so my brother is truly...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.85,0:15:59.32,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So, he's "the hero who\Nsaved Yogo" now, is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.32,0:16:01.79,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's quite a change\Nof heart you've had.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.19,0:16:07.50,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Female bodyguard,\Nour interests now coincide.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.13,0:16:10.37,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I realize that we may not\Nhave always seen eye to eye...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.37,0:16:13.84,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...but these men no longer\Nmean you any harm.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.50,0:16:21.64,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Star reader. Your words may sound noble,\Nbut if we now share a common goal...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.64,0:16:25.85,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...cut to the chase and\Ntell us how to kill the Rarunga.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.95,0:16:29.15,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A Rarunga's weakness is fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.15,0:16:31.59,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It was written in the epitaphs\Nthat the Warriors Eight...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.59,0:16:35.89,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...who served the founding father\Ndrove off the Rarunga using fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.63,0:16:41.63,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now I see! it's a question of\Nrelative strengths between spirits.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.20,0:16:45.47,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Water is beaten by earth,\Nand earth is beaten by fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.93,0:16:50.84,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Rarunga, which devour the egg of the\Nwater spirit...are they earth spirits?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.74,0:16:56.81,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Damn, I can't believe I didn't\Nmake such a simple connection...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.55,0:17:01.62,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then the torches used in the summer\Nsolstice festival are vestiges of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.62,0:17:02.78,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.99,0:17:07.96,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And now, 200 years later,\Nthat duty has once again fallen to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.52,0:17:11.63,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So, you are the descendants\Nof the Warriors Eight.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.70,0:17:18.77,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Chagum?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.80,0:17:23.61,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Chagum!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.51,0:17:27.68,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Incredible!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.01,0:17:29.81,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The power of the egg?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.55,0:17:33.95,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! Don't do anything rash.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.95,0:17:37.99,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Torogai, it was written\Nthat the egg is to be born...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.99,0:17:41.62,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...on the night of the spring equinox\Nwhen the double moon rises.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.16,0:17:45.99,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Nightfall is still far off.\NWhat, then, is causing...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.53,0:17:50.33,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No idea. I don't know\Nwhat's going to happen either.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.67,0:17:52.90,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You'd best be on\Nyour guard, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.61,0:17:57.41,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Chagum...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.99,0:18:15.76,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What in the world is he doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.76,0:18:22.30,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We were wrong...\NWe were mistaken, Shuga!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.10,0:18:26.13,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How can this be?\NWhy did we learn this only now?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.60,0:18:28.00,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How many tablets are left!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.74,0:18:32.51,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There should be eight remaining.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.51,0:18:35.68,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Bring them all up in one go!\NGo summon the retrieval team!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.38,0:18:40.68,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But, master, we can't make them\Ndive so many times in a single day.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.92,0:18:42.95,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Where does your duty lie?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.12,0:18:45.79,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Will you read the stars\Nin a destroyed nation?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.86,0:18:49.89,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Prince Sagum,\Ngrant me your protection...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.26,0:18:54.40,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Chagum, are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.04,0:19:06.44,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This sense of malice...\Nit's not natural.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.81,0:19:09.65,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is it something from Nayug?\NBut where is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.69,0:19:23.86,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.43,0:19:28.80,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is that a Rarunga?\NIs that the egg-eater?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.84,0:19:36.97,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Light your weapons!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.15,0:19:48.25,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Take position!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.35,0:19:53.99,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You people stay back!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.31,0:20:11.64,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My senses, they're...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.98,0:20:23.99,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Chagum!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.05,0:20:25.09,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.45,0:20:55.58,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is it dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.79,0:20:58.02,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's still here!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.22,0:21:34.19,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Chagum?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.30,0:21:50.34,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Chagum!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.71,0:21:56.61,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Chagum!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.69,0:22:04.59,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Highness!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.89,0:22:07.59,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Where does that boy\Nthink he's going?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.66,0:22:12.83,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Master Gakai!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.27,0:22:25.77,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shuga, Aoike isn't\Nthe land of feasting...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.11,0:22:27.28,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Master Gakai!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.14,0:22:33.58,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,S-Send these tablets\Nto Shuga at Aoike!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.55,0:22:37.52,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He should be able to\Ndecipher them on the spot...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.95,0:22:40.62,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If the messenger rides at top speed,\Nhe'll make it in time!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.06,0:22:42.22,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Master Gakai...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.72,0:23:13.05,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As I sat huddled and alone, holding\Nback the tears on those nights...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.05,0:23:20.20,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When it felt like I was about\Nto succumb to my doubts...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.20,0:23:25.47,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...there you were,\Nat my side before I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.47,0:23:32.81,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It was none other than you\Nwho was there for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.81,0:23:47.09,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I keep wishing, "I want to be strong."\NI stumble and hurt myself again.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.09,0:23:56.46,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But because I have you to believe in,\NI can get back to my feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.46,0:24:03.24,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I simply want to tell\Nmy dear one, "Thank you. "
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.24,0:24:08.38,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,At the top of my lungs,\Nagain and again.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.38,0:24:16.75,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I call out to my precious loved one.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.75,0:24:20.96,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is my voice reaching you?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.96,0:24:29.20,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In this world that always changes,\Nhuman warmth never does.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.20,0:24:39.51,ED,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm certain I sensed the presence\Nof the one that I hold dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.01,0:24:45.48,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Next Time
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.21,0:24:45.81,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,They have finally made\Npeace with each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.15,0:24:49.88,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,However, the missing epitaphs\Nturn everything on its head.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.45,0:24:53.05,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, "The Last Hope."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.02,0:24:57.03,Signs,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 24\NThe Last Hope
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.69,0:24:56.62,Dialogue,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tanda's courage\Nkeeps their hopes alive.
